# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok massachusetts sen.-elect scott brown says he 'd like daughter <unk> to have another crack at `` american idol , '' where judge simon cowell once described her performance as robotic and empty .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Scott"
                  :op2 "Brown")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (s2 / state
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Massachusetts"))
                  :ARG2 (s3 / senator)))
      :ARG1 (l / like-02
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (c / crack-01
                  :ARG0 (p2 / person
                        :ARG0-of (h2 / have-rel-role-91
                              :ARG1 p
                              :ARG2 (d / daughter)))
                  :ARG1 (ii / idol
                        :mod (c2 / country
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "America"))
                        :location-of (d2 / describe-01
                              :ARG0 (p3 / person
                                    :name (n4 / name
                                          :op1 "Simon"
                                          :op2 "Celtell")
                                    :ARG0-of (h3 / have-org-role-91
                                          :ARG3 (j / judge-01)))
                              :ARG1 (p4 / perform-01
                                    :ARG0 p2)
                              :ARG2 (a / and
                                    :op1 (r / robot)
                                    :op2 (e / empty))
                              :time (o / once)))
                  :mod (a2 / another))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the walt disney co. understandably has thrown enormous resources into selling `` the village , '' one of its last , best chances at salvaging a movie year that has so far been marked by one embarrassment after another .
# ::alignments
(t / throw-01
      :ARG0 (c / company
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Walt"
                  :op2 "Dasney"
                  :op3 "Co."))
      :ARG1 (r / resource
            :mod (e / enormous))
      :ARG2 (s / sell-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (v / village
                  :ARG1-of (c2 / chance-02
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG2 (s2 / salvage-01
                              :ARG0 c
                              :ARG1 (y / year
                                    :mod (m / movie)
                                    :ARG1-of (m2 / mark-02
                                          :ARG0 (e2 / embarrass-01
                                                :quant 1
                                                :mod (a / after
                                                      :op1 (a2 / another)))
                                          :time (s3 / so-far)))
                              :mod (l / last))
                        :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                              :ARG2 (g / good-02
                                    :ARG1 c2)
                              :ARG3 (m3 / most)))))
      :ARG1-of (u / understand-01
            :ARG1-of (p / possible-01)))

                                                            :op1 "Parliament")

                                                                  :ARG1 (p / parliament)

                                                            :weekday (f / friday)))))))
                        :ARG1-of (l3 / legal-02)
                        :mod (s3 / some)))))

            :ARG1 (w / way
                  :purpose (d2 / deploy-01

                                          :op1 "Africa")))))))

# ::id 6 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok i 've never been a big fan of store-bought greeting cards .
# ::alignments

      :polarity -
      :mod (b / big)
      :topic (c / card
            :instrument-of (g / greet-01)
            :ARG1-of (b2 / buy-01
                  :ARG0 (s / store)))
      :domain (ii / i)
      :time (e / ever))

# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (f / forecast
            :ARG1-of (p / publish-01
                  :time (d / date-entity
                        :weekday (t / thursday))))
      :ARG1 (e / expect-01
            :ARG1 (r / reach-01
                  :ARG0 (m / market
                        :mod (g / game)
                        :location (c / country
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "China"))
                        :mod (o / online))
                  :ARG1 (m2 / monetary-quantity
                        :quant 1000000000
                        :unit (d2 / dollar))
                  :topic (a / and
                        :op1 (g2 / grow-01
                              :ARG1 (p2 / person
                                    :ARG0-of (u / use-01
                                          :ARG1 (ii / internet)))
                              :manner (r2 / rapid))
                        :op2 (l / launch-01
                              :ARG1 (g3 / game
                                    :ARG1-of (n2 / new-01)
                                    :mod (q / quality
                                          :ARG1-of (h / high-02))))))))

            :ARG0 p)
      :ARG2 (f2 / funeral
            :poss (r3 / ranger
                  :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                        :value 1)
                  :mod (f3 / female)
                  :ARG1-of (k2 / kill-01
                        :ARG0 (ii / insurgency
                              :mod (v / violent)
                              :mod (r4 / religious-group
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Muslim")))
                        :location s2))))

# ::id 1817 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok times sports columnist boston scott kazmir confirmed joe maddon was a genius thursday night .
# ::alignments
(c / confirm-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Boston"
                  :op2 "Scott"
                  :op3 "Kazmir")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (n2 / newspaper
                        :name (n3 / name
                              :op1 "The"
                              :op2 "Times"))
                  :ARG2 (c2 / columnist
                        :topic (s / sport))))
      :ARG1 (g / genius
            :domain (p2 / person
                  :name (n4 / name
                        :op1 "Joe"
                        :op2 "Maddon"))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (t / thursday)
                  :dayperiod (n5 / night))))

# ::id 1818 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok dutchman ids postma claimed a gold medal in the <unk> and a silver in the #,### friday to help him a commanding lead in the all-round european speedskating championships in <unk> , the netherlands .
# ::alignments
(c / claim-02
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Dutchman")
            :ARG0-of (p2 / post-02))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (m / medal
                  :mod (g / gold)
                  :topic (e / event
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "The"
                              :op2 "Phoenix")))
            :op2 (m2 / medal
                  :mod (s / silver)
                  :topic (e2 / event
                        :name (n3 / name
                              :op1 "The"
                              :op2 "Phoenix"))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday))
      :purpose (h / help-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (l / lead-02
                  :ARG0 p
                  :ARG1-of (c2 / command-02)
                  :topic (g2 / game
                        :name (n4 / name
                              :op1 "European"
                              :op2 "Speedskating"
                              :op3 "Championships")
                        :location (c3 / country-region
                              :name (n5 / name
                                    :op1 "The"
                                    :op2 "Netherlands"))
                        :mod (r / round
                              :mod (a2 / all))))
            :ARG2 p))

# ::id 1819 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok brazilian and venezuelan business leaders on saturday asked their presidents to form a free trade zone for the two countries that could accelerate the process of creating a similar zone for all of south america .
# ::alignments
(a / ask-02
      :ARG0 (a2 / and
            :op1 (p / person
                  :ARG0-of (l / lead-02
                        :ARG1 (c / country
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Brazil"))
                        :ARG2 (b / business)))
            :op2 (p2 / person
                  :ARG0-of (l2 / lead-02
                        :ARG1 (c2 / country
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Venezuela"))
                        :ARG2 b)))
      :ARG1 (f / form-01
            :ARG0 (p3 / person
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 a2
                        :ARG2 (p4 / president)))
            :ARG1 (z / zone
                  :ARG1-of (f2 / free-04)
                  :mod (t / trade-01)
                  :beneficiary a2)
            :ARG0-of (a3 / accelerate-01
                  :ARG1 (p5 / process-02
                        :ARG1 (c3 / create-01
                              :ARG1 (z2 / zone
                                    :ARG1-of (r / resemble-01))
                              :beneficiary (c4 / country
                                    :part-of (s / south
                                          :part-of (c5 / country
                                                :name (n3 / name
                                                      :op1 "America")))
                                    :mod (a4 / all))))
                  :ARG1-of (p6 / possible-01)))
      :ARG2 p3
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (s2 / saturday)))
